march 31 2010 to school of medicine faculty and staff from marcia cohen senior associate dean for finance and administration subject winter closure 2010 dear colleagues i am writing about the school of medicine's 2010 winter closure schedule for the december 2010 holiday season the school of medicine will follow the same schedule which was approved by president hennessy and provost etchemendy for the university as in the past we are providing information about the winter break schedule so that employees including bargaining unit employees have advance notice of these dates and can plan accordingly the 2010 winter closure will be monday december 20 2010 through friday december 31 2010 reopening with the start of business on monday january 3 2011 all areas of the school of medicine are asked to close during this two week period as in past years there will be some areas of the school of medicine that must remain open for all or part of the winter closure ie clinical units lab animal facilities some research labs portions of student affairs lane library etc dfa's or department directors are expected to review requests for employees to work during winter closure and approve only those that are critical to departmental operations the university will provide one 1 additional day off with pay which the school of medicine has designated as thursday december 30 2010 for the other regular workdays during winter close that are not designated by the university as holidays or a paid day off employees may use accrued vacation time any available pto approved time off without pay or any combination thereof all departments are asked to administer time off during this week in a consistent fashion and not to award university paid time off for other dates december 20 2010 pto floating holiday vacation or unpaid time off december 21 2010 pto floating holiday vacation or unpaid time off december 22 2010 pto floating holiday vacation or unpaid time off december 23 2010 university holiday december 24 2010 university holiday december 27 2010 pto floating holiday vacation or unpaid time off december 28 2010 pto floating holiday vacation or unpaid time off december 29 2010 pto floating holiday vacation or unpaid time off december 30 2010 university paid day off december 31 2010 university holiday employees may borrow accrued time posted in axess timecard in january 2011 pto floating holiday vacation accrual if needed this is expected to apply to those employees who are relatively new and have not had the opportunity to build up accrued time to use during winter closure any decision to keep a department open must be approved by the dfa and or department director overseeing the department and hrg employee relations must be notified in those rare cases where operations require that some employees remain on duty in a unit that is otherwise closed hrg employee relations in conjunction with the dfa and or department director may approve an alternative paid day off for those employees who are required to work for operational reasons please communicate the plans for your departments to all employees as soon as possible so that they may make appropriate plans for the use of their accrued vacation and pto if you have questions regarding the school of medicine winter closure schedule please contact human resource group employee relations at 5 8615 or you may reply to this email to reach norma leavitt should you have any questions cc philip pizzo md cori bossenberry
